<title>UK: Cadbury up on Pepsico link talk.</title>
<headline>Cadbury up on Pepsico link talk.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Cadbury Schweppes Plc rose on Friday as reports of a restructuring at Pepsico Inc revived speculation the U.S. drinks and food group could be interested in the British company, dealers said.</p>
<p>Cadbury shares were up 7-1/2p or 1.4 percent at 524p by 0808 GMT, while the overall market was up 0.27 percent.</p>
<p>&quot;These rumours surface every time you get a major shake-up in the food industry,&quot; one market maker said.</p>
<p>A second noted that Cadbury earlier this month accepted the resignation of board member Karl von der Heyden who is moving to Pepsico as vice chairman and chief financial officer.  </p>
<p>&quot;That move created a link in people's minds. Whether there's anything more to it remains to be seen,&quot; he said.</p>
